1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
Start on the exact operational screen for this guide.

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,000
Insurance is a pickup gate, not just a policy list.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Use the status tiles to spot pending binds and bind failures first.

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,000
Filter bind failures when a customer may have paid but no policy was issued.

5
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,500
Verify driver, vehicle, dates, tier, premium, markup, charged amount, and status.

6
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,000
Recent activity explains provider errors that must be reconciled before pickup.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,500
Do not proceed if the driver, vehicle, dates, or coverage limits do not match the booking.

8
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,000
Insurance is a pickup gate; approve only clean coverage.
